  <summary date="2022-07-20T19:33:08Z" status="Introduced in House">Targeting Resources for Equitable Access to Treatment for Long COVID Act or the TREAT Long COVID Act

This bill requires the Department of Health and Human Services to award competitive grants to create or expand the capacity of clinics that treat patients with persistent, long-term symptoms following recovery from acute COVID-19 (i.e., Long COVID). Eligible recipients include federally qualified health centers, rural health clinics, urban Indian health centers, and state and local health departments.</summary>
